erty (other than the Works), which may arise out of or in consequence of the exccution and completion of the Works and the remedying of any defects therein, and against all claims, proceedings, damages, costs, charges and expenses whatsoever in respect thereof or in relation thereto, subject to the exceptions defined in Sub-Clause 22.2. The “exceptions” referred to in Sub-Clause 22.1 are: (a) the permanent use or occupation of land by the Works, or any part thereof, (b) the right of the Employer to execute the Works, or any part thercof, on, over, under, in or through any land, (c) damage to property which is the unavoidable result of the execution and completion of the Works, or the remedying of any defects therein, i', '6d6512d8', 'text', NULL, 1250, '{"group":"C"}'::jsonb);
